verses.verse: When Israel came out of Egypt, and the house of Iacob from amonge that straung people.
Iuda was his Sanctuary, and Israell his domynion.
The see sawe that, and fled Iordan was dryuen backe.
The mountaynes skipped lyke rammes, and the lytle hilles lyke yonge shepe.
What ayleth the, O thou see, that thou fleddest? and thou Iordan, that thou wast dryuen backe?
Ye mountaynes, that ye skypped lyke rammes: & ye lytle hylles, lyke yong shepe?
Tremble thou erth at the presence of the Lord, at the presence of the God of Iacob.
Which turned the hard rocke in to a standynge water, and the flynt stone into a spryngynge well.
